                <div class="wpb_wrapper">
            
    <div class="wpb_text_column wpb_content_element ">
        <div class="wpb_wrapper">
            <p><span style="font-weight: 400;">The venture capital market is changing so it is now easier to get involved in venture capital in Sydney. Traditionally a company wanting to raise funds via retail crowdsource funding opportunities had to be structured as a public company (unlisted) but in September 2017, legislation changed extending the crowdsource funding opportunities to proprietary companies. The new rules allow private companies to not count crowd-sourced funding investors towards the 50-shareholder cap. With the new legislation comes additional governance and reporting obligations that are designed to protect investors.&nbsp;</span></p>

        </div>
    </div>

        </div>
              </div>
            </div>


            <div class="col-md-6">
              <div class="inner-container px-3 px-md-4 py-3">
                  
                  <div class="wpb_wrapper">
            
    <div class="wpb_text_column wpb_content_element ">
        
        <div class="wpb_wrapper">
            <p><span style="font-weight: 400;">And recent changes have made it easier for investors too. Changes to Australian legislation in 2017 mean that investment opportunities that had previously only been available to high net worth individuals or sophisticated investors can now be accessed by retail investors. Retail investors who meet certain criteria are now able to invest up to $10,000 in private companies. This means startup investment is no longer just for venture capitalists or </span><a href="https://www.venturecrowd.com.au/s/angel-investing/"><span style="font-weight: 400;">angel investing</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> but is more accessible to everyday investors who can now co-invest on the same economic terms alongside experienced lead investors. This means that investors can now have direct access to alternative investment opportunities that have previously been limited to institutional or sophisticated investors.</span></p>

        </div>
    </div>
        </div>

              </div>
            </div> 
          </div>
            
            


